The paper deals with multi-label classification in the context of medical imaging, which is a common application area for computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method is a deep learning approach that involves optimizing a loss function, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of different datasets and evaluation metrics, which are common topics in natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM).
